title: Remember when you called me stupid?
Soup Spoon
description: Still to this day one of the most unhinged pictures you've ever sent me, and I absolutely loved it.

title: Pasta
description: You making pasta is such an amazing memory for me. I loved how happy you were, and how much you loved learning and doing it. It was also the first time I realized that I don't have to hate having someone else in the kitchen with me. It felt so normal to co-exist with you, and it still does to this day.

title: Rock
description: Sitting on our rock looking out. Can't wait to take polaroids of us there.

title: Edmonton Pt. 1
description: One of my all-time favourite photos of us. It always makes me happy to know how happy I am to be with you, and how happy you look to be with me.

title: Edmonton - Car Noms
description: Having a late breakfast outside in the parking lot of Starbucks, eating leftovers from the Melting Pot. Top tier happy vibes.

title: Polaroids
description: A small sub-section of our polaroids together. And also, still my phone background, and probably will be until I find something better with us.

title: Ranchlands
description: Going to Ranchlands and seeing where you lived, walking around the school you used to go to, and reliving those memories with you is such a highlight. And getting to show you where my aunt and grandma used to live too.

title: Horseback Riding
description: Loved horseback riding with you. It was nice to be out and about, doing something I absolutely love with someone I love more than anything.

title: Horse
description: It's you. You're the horse. Look at them ears.

title: Pond Pt 1.
description: First time seeing a non-domesticated beaver for both of us.

title: Fall Out Boy
description: One of my favourite photos, and the first concert we went to. It was loud, overwhelming, but always fun because it was with you.

title: Just because this is cute as fuck.
Pandora
description: One of the many things we match with.

title: Hot Pot
description: One of my all-time favourite places to go with you. It always feels warm and happy and like home, just like you.

title: Foot Horrors
description: The start of the foot horrors. The very first foot picture I have on my phone from you. Certainly not the last.
